\n**WHAT'S GOING ON**\nVanta, a company that helps businesses prove they are secure, swapped out their old text-reading software for a smarter tool called Reducto [1, 5]. Instead of just dumbly extracting words from a page, this new AI actually reads complex security questionnaires, figures out the right answers, and writes those answers directly back into the original file [2, 3]. It even keeps the original formatting exactly intact [3]. Vanta is also using this system as an internal judge to look at screenshots of security settings and decide if the evidence is actually good enough to show an auditor [6, 7]. \n\n**WHY THIS IS A BIG DEAL**\nIf you want to sell software to a large corporation, they force you to fill out a massive, tedious spreadsheet to prove you won't accidentally leak their data [2]. Historically, answering these questionnaires has been a soul-crushing exercise in copying and pasting from old reports [2]. Before, an AI might help you find the right text, but a human still had to do the manual labor of pasting it back into the maze of boxes [3]. By using what Reducto calls an \"Edit endpoint,\" the AI isn't just reading anymore; it is acting [3]. It turns the machine from a passive observer into an active participant that can fill out the form itself [3]. This proves that AI agents are finally moving beyond just chatting with us\u2014they are starting to push the buttons and do the actual, physical busywork of the digital world. \n\n**UNCOMFORTABLE TRUTH**\nThe thing nobody wants to admit is that a massive pillar of modern corporate security is built on people emailing messy PDFs, poorly formatted spreadsheets, and blurry PowerPoint screenshots to each other [1, 2]. It is a house of cards made of digital paperwork. Older software tools choked because real-world business data isn't clean; it is incredibly sloppy [1]. The real friction here is that we aren't using cutting-edge AI to solve brilliant new problems\u2014we are forced to use it to decipher terrible formatting and do the mindless bureaucratic box-checking that humans shouldn't have been subjected to in the first place [1, 4]. \n\n**SO WHAT**\nAI has officially graduated from just reading your messy documents to actually doing your tedious paperwork for you [3].",
